{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place cod fillets skin-side down in a saucepan and add 150 g of water. Cover and simmer until fillets begin to bleach and foam, then turn off heat and keep covered for 2 minutes. Transfer fillets to an oven-proof dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm) and reserve cooking liquid.","Place oil in mixing bowl and heat <nobr>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add garlic and cayenne pepper then sauté <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Pour through a fine sieve, reserve oil and set aside.","Preheat oven to 200°C.","Place half of sautéed garlic and 50 g of reserved cooking liquid from saucepan in mixing bowl then blend <nobr>2 min\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, place remaining sautéed garlic over cod fillets. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then stir <nobr>2 min\/speed 4<\/nobr> while slowly pouring reserved oil onto mixing bowl lid. Once combined, pour over cod.","Place remaining 300 g water in mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, weigh in spinach, sprinkle with salt then cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Bake cod for 8 minutes (200°C).","Arrange steamed spinach on serving plates, place cod fillets on top and drizzle with liquid caramel."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 cod fillets, boneless (approx. 100 g each)","450 g water","200 g extra virgin olive oil","15 garlic cloves","3 pinches ground cayenne pepper","300 g fresh spinach leaves","&frac18; tsp fine sea salt","20 g liquid caramel"]}],"id":"r144272","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-WZZM1zmTsLs\/XZVPg8kasMI\/AAAAAAAAc5o\/t7Fg1lE17qIexW7cCDqdkmlniWE5mx1eQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7jwua8E-qBKNUPVS.png","title":"Cod with Garlic Caramel Sauce","publishedAt":"2017-03-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21.7 g","fat":"51.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"8.3 g","calories":"2437 kJ \/ 583 kcal"},"usefulItems":"oven-proof dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm), slotted spoon, saucepan, fine sieve, hob, oven","basicInfo":["easy","15m",